body_html:
@pbilling thanks for the tags info. Looks like you have Mac OS X 10.10 installed. The pypi binary requires to have at least 10.11. One workaround is that you can try our uploaded binaries here. For example:
pip install https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/tensorflow-1.2.0rc0-py2-none-any.whl

body:
@pbilling thanks for the tags info. Looks like you have Mac OS X 10.10 installed. The pypi binary requires to have at least 10.11. One workaround is that you can try our uploaded binaries [here](https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_mac#python_27). For example:
`pip install https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/mac/cpu/tensorflow-1.2.0rc0-py2-none-any.whl`
